# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: bolib: collection, string, refcount, and timer bugs
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* TODO [#A] bolib: memory and refcount bugs  :bolib:memory:objc:

** Findings

*** [critical] BoListNoRetain removeObjectAt: reads one past the array (BoListNoRetain.m:212-213)
=while(idx<count){ elements[idx]=elements[idx+1]; INC(idx); }= reads
=elements[count]= when =idx==count-1= (OOB when =count==capacity=), before
=count-- =. Fix: bound =idx<count-1= (BoArray.m:182 already does this right).
Same family as BcList/bjarray/BpList.

*** [critical] BoString insert:at: overlapping memcpy + use-after-free on self-insert (BoString.m:189-195)
- =BcMem_Copy= maps to =memcpy= (non-overlapping), but =insert:at:= uses it to
  shift the tail forward over itself → corruption. Use a backward-safe move
  (memmove semantics), and ensure capacity is =nLength+1=.
- If =substring == self= (e.g. =[s insert:s at:0]= / =append:= of self),
  =setCapacity:…copy:TRUE= reallocates =self->data=, freeing =substring->data=;
  the later =BcMem_Copy(substring->data,…)= reads freed memory. Guard against
  aliasing (copy the substring first, or detect =substring==self=).

*** [high] BoObject release: pool has no dedup → possible double-free (BoObject.m:262-270)
=release= re-adds the object to =deletePool= on reaching 0, but the pool is not
deduplicated; over-release / mixed free paths can enqueue the same pointer
twice, freed twice in =deleteObjects=. Add membership tracking or a =<0= guard
that raises.

*** [high] Dangling dependants on free (BoObject.m free / changed:)
An object freed via =DeletePool deleteObjects= is not removed from *other*
objects' =_dependants= lists, leaving dangling pointers; a later =changed:=
sends to a freed object. Fix: on free, unregister from all dependees, or have
=_dependants= hold weak back-references that are cleared.

*** [medium] getString: has no destination size → caller-buffer overflow (BoString.m:144-149)
Copies =length+NUL= into a caller =char*= with no capacity parameter; any
smaller buffer overflows. API defect — add a max-size parameter (or return an
allocated/Bc string).

*** [medium] position:from: unbounded inner scan (BoString.m:232-235)
Inner loop is not bounded by =substring->length=; relies on NUL terminators and
can over-read. Bound =i= by =substring->length=.

*** [medium] changed: passes a long as id via perform:with:with: (BoObject.m:316)
=(id)cause= casts a =long= to a pointer and the receiver reads it back as =long=
— correct only by LP64 coincidence and ABI luck (see perform: note below). Use a
typed dispatch rather than =perform:with:with:= for the integer =cause=.

*** [low] BoCompat -perform: calls the IMP untyped (BoObject.m:72-91)
=IMP imp=objc_msg_lookup(...); return(imp(self,sel,…));= is fine for all-=id=
selectors on x86-64/ARM64, but selectors taking/returning struct/float/non-=id=
args are mis-called (ABI). Cast the IMP to the correct signature per arity, and
prefer not to route non-=id= payloads (the =cause= long) through =perform:=.

*** [low] copy always yields a non-retaining BoListNoRetain (BoListNoRetain.m:58-65)
=-copy= hardcodes =[[BoListNoRetain alloc]…]=, so copying a =BoList= loses retain
semantics and shares object pointers without retaining them. Use =[self class]=
and respect the subclass's retain behaviour.

*** [low] BoTimer.posix.m does not compile / wrong APIs
- =#include <pthreads.h= is unterminated (missing =>=) — fatal on its own.
- Uses Mach =cthread_*=/=mutex_*=/=condition_*= and 4.2BSD =sigvec=/=sigblock=
  rather than POSIX =pthread=/=sigaction=, and passes =SIGALRM= where
  =setitimer= expects =ITIMER_REAL=. The "posix" file is effectively NeXT/Mach.
It is currently commented out of the Makefile (=#OBJCSOURCES += BoTimer.posix.m=);
either port it properly to POSIX or mark it clearly unsupported.

** Doc bug
=BoArray.h:60-68= =resize:= PRE says =newSize>[self size]=, but the
implementation (BoArray.m:119-124) explicitly handles shrinking. Fix the header.

** Plan
1. Fix removeObjectAt: bound; fix BoString insert (memmove + aliasing guard).
2. Add pool dedup / over-release guard; fix dangling-dependants on free.
3. Give getString: a size parameter; bound position:from:.
4. Type the perform: IMP calls; stop routing =cause= through perform:.
5. Decide BoTimer.posix fate (port or remove); fix the resize: doc.

   DECISION:
   - Rename the files BoTimer-posix.m  BoTimer-macintosh.m BoTimer-next.m, and
   - implement BoTimer-posix.m on posix systems.

As a general rule, file names should avoid having more than one dot; use dashes (minus-sign) as word separators in file names.











